<h1>Art Werschulz</h1>

<!WA0><IMG ALIGN=right SRC="http://www.cs.columbia.edu/~agw/agw.gif" WIDTH=186 HEIGHT=153 ALT="">
<P>

<em> Netsurfers are encouraged to jump to my
<!WA1><a href="http://www.cs.columbia.edu/~agw/hotlist.html">hotlist</a>.</em>

<hr>

<p>

My "real" position is Professor of Computer Science at
<!WA2><a href="http://dsm.fordham.edu/~agw/">
Fordham University</a>
(Fordham College at Lincoln Center, to be precise).
I have been a Visiting Scholar in the 
<!WA3><a href="http://www.cs.columbia.edu/">
Columbia University Computer Science Department</a> 
since 1982.

<P>

I do work in 
<!WA4><a href="http://www.cs.columbia.edu/~agw/ibc">information-based complexity</a>.
My special interests include the following:

<UL>
<LI> Complexity of partial differential equations.
<LI> Complexity of integral equations.
<LI> Complexity of ill-posed problems.
</UL>

Here are some recent papers.

<UL>
<LI>
  <!WA5><A HREF="ftp://ftp.cs.columbia.edu/reports/reports-1996/cucs-035-96.ps.gz">
  The complexity of definite elliptic problems with noisy data
  </A>

<LI>
  <!WA6><A HREF="ftp://ftp.cs.columbia.edu/reports/reports-1995/cucs-016-95.ps.gz">
  The complexity of the Poisson problem for spaces of bounded mixed derivatives
  </A>

<LI>
  <!WA7><A HREF="ftp://ftp.cs.columbia.edu/reports/reports-1995/cucs-009-95.ps.gz">
  What is the complexity of solution-restricted operator equations?
  </A>

<LI>
  <!WA8><A HREF="ftp://ftp.cs.columbia.edu/reports/reports-1994/cucs-016-94.ps.Z">
  The complexity of multivariate elliptic problems with analytic data
  </A>

</UL>

I also maintain
<!WA9><a href="http://www.cs.columbia.edu/cacnet">CAC-NET/FoCM-NET</a>,
an electronic conferencing system for researchers in continuous algorithms and
complexity and in foundations of computational mathematics. 

